review_blob: This is delicious. My wife embarrassingly enjoys Younger of Alloa's Sweetheart Stout which is basically a 2% abv cola. I've been trying to find a milk stout to satisfy her sweet tooth, and this has done the trick. It's delicious - did I already say that??
Bought this to use in my winter stew. Kept some by for tasting. Really nice malty aromas, smooth and easy to drink. Nice.
Right, I wasn't keen on this but I think that was more down to my uneducated palate than anything else. It was very strong, and heavy where I prefer something a bit lighter.
I thought this was nice. Again first beer I've tasted from this brewery, I look forward to trying more.
Lovely and smooth, moreish. Again, I tried this in BrewDog Bar Glasgow. So glad they had this as a guest.
This is my one of my favourite session beers, it's hoppy, easy to drink, it smells good, goes great with a lot of different foods, total winner.
This is one of the most exciting beers Ive tasted so far. The hibiscus really zings! Its tangy and refreshing and delicious beer.
beer_name: Brew By Numbers 01/09 Saison - Hibiscus & Chamomile

review_blob: Tried this the other night in BrewDog Bar Glasgow. Tasty! I'd never tried anything from Evil Twin before.
I thought this tasted great, really moreish! I thought the aroma was pleasant too, a citrus smell, with a sweetness and a slight hint of alcohol.
